vil life, and, in a religious context, how Hegel saw considerations of authority and guilt sublimated and purified in the development of Christianity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Hegel. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy of Religion. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aWalker, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847159440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438471594423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438471594/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles